There is nothing to the app, it doesn't easily help you play or count and from the one game I attempted to set up for, the calculation was wrong.

Functional, but clumsy and not very intuitive. I find it very difficult to set up scenarios with multiple different weapons firing at the target. Sometimes the results just refuse to update or give back 0s even when all required fields are filled correctly. Being able to save profiles is nice in theory, but I'd prefer it if the basic UI and features had been implemented better first.
Great tool
Terrible UI, extremely unintuitive to use.

Hey Jake! I love the app, but I wanted to leave you some feedback. Sometime when I go to change the tags of a unit from the Manage Profiles tab, the app stutters for a moment then moves me into the "Home" tab. It makes the app feel unpolished and buggy. I'm not sure the reason, but I only noticed it happening after I had added several profiles(20+). Additionally, it would be nice if you could set the parameters or filter the outcome of an analysis (I.G. filter by best ROI, or best damage, ect.

content: Great app which follows steps of origin web version. Some convenient features are missing, though, such as resetting current input, preset profiles or at least MEQ/TEQ/GEQ.
